                    "description": "Eaton is a global technology leader in power management solutions\nthat make electrical, hydraulic and mechanical power operate more efficiently, reliably, safely and sustainably. The headquarter in Europe is located in Hengelo (NL)\n\n2006-2010 Operational Excellence Program Manager\nWith a team of 12 engineers, we improved business processes by using different improvement tools (Business Excellence assessments, creative acceleration tools, future search, Quality improvement&assurance, Lean, 6Sigma, VAVE tools, etc).\nWhile we always looked at total Value Streams, we spend a lot of time in other European countries.\n\n2004-2006 Maintenance Manager\nWith a team of 10 maintenance-engineers, we maintained and improved the production and assembly processes (sheetmetal, turning/milling, (injection)moulding and automated assembly lines). We used methodologies like RCMII and ITIL to get the best reliability. Our support focussed on Hengelo NL, Hungary and Denmark.\n\n2000-2004 Accountmanager Toolshop\nThe toolshop was build on both internal and external orders. I was in the lead of the external orderflow, from acquisition upto completion. The toolshop was mainly focussed on multi-component injectionmouls and uses high-tech machines (high speed milling, 3D scanning, etc)\n\n1998-2000 Product- and processengineer Sheetmetal\nMy main responsibility was to design and optimize sheetmetal production-processes. I lead projects in logistics (automated storage of sheetmetal), new product development (welding robot cells) and improving existing processes using lean and 6-sigma (powdercoatlines)\n\nFind more about Eaton at Eaton.com",
